# Fullstack Testing Strategy (Enterprise)

Use this rule when user asks for testing architecture, test plan, test checklist, go-live quality audit, or reliability hardening.

## Required Output Sections
- Testing philosophy and pyramid rationale.
- Backend testing strategy.
- Frontend testing strategy.
- Test data strategy.
- CI/CD integration and quality gates.
- Coverage guidance and flaky-test prevention.
- Testing best practices and production-readiness checklist.

## 1) Testing Philosophy
- Explain unit/integration/e2e test pyramid with speed-vs-confidence tradeoffs.
- Prioritize deterministic, reliable, and fast feedback loops.
- Emphasize maintainability of tests as first-class engineering concern.

## 2) Backend Testing (Spring Boot)
- Cover:
  - unit tests (service/domain logic)
  - repository tests (real DB with Testcontainers)
  - controller/API tests (MockMvc/RestAssured)
  - integration tests (cross-layer behavior)
- Preferred tools:
  - JUnit
  - Mockito
  - Testcontainers
  - RestAssured

## 3) Backend Rules
- Service logic must have unit tests.
- Repository behavior must be validated against containerized DB.
- Controller tests must verify status, payload shape, and auth/error behavior.
- Use realistic fixtures/factories instead of brittle hardcoded data.

## 4) Database Integration Testing
- Use Testcontainers with database matching production profile whenever possible.
- Validate migrations, constraints, transaction behavior, and query correctness.
- Explain why containerized DB tests are more reliable than pure in-memory substitutes.

## 5) API Testing
- Validate:
  - status codes
  - response schema
  - error responses
  - authentication/authorization
- Use RestAssured for contract-level and scenario-level assertions.

## 6) Frontend Testing (React + Next.js)
- Cover:
  - unit tests
  - component tests
  - integration tests
  - e2e tests
- Preferred tools:
  - Jest
  - React Testing Library
  - MSW
  - Playwright or Cypress

## 7) Frontend Rules
- Component tests verify render, interaction, and accessibility expectations.
- Form tests verify validation, submission, and error states.
- Use MSW for isolated API behavior without brittle network coupling.

## 8) End-to-End Tests
- Validate critical user journeys (for example login -> create transaction -> verify outcome).
- Keep e2e suite focused on high-value paths.
- Avoid duplicating all unit/integration coverage in e2e layer.

## 9) Test Data Strategy
- Use factories, fixtures, and seed scripts.
- Avoid implicit coupling to hardcoded brittle records.
- Keep test data deterministic and scenario-focused.

## 10) CI/CD Testing Integration
- Pipeline sequence should include:
  - build
  - unit tests
  - integration tests
  - e2e tests
- Enforce failure gates: block deploy on failed mandatory stages.

## 11) Coverage Guidance
- Recommend directional thresholds:
  - backend service coverage > 80%
  - frontend component coverage > 70%
- Clarify that meaningful coverage and behavior confidence are more important than 100% raw numbers.

## 12) Flaky Test Prevention
- Avoid time-based assertions.
- Avoid uncontrolled external network dependency.
- Use deterministic test data and explicit waiting strategies.

## 13) Output Quality Rules
- Provide practical tool recommendations by test layer.
- Include concise code examples when requested.
- Prefer actionable architecture decisions over generic testing advice.
